data.chText: （系船用的）缆绳；（支撑桥梁等用的）钢索
data.enText: thick strong metal rope used on ships, for supporting bridges, etc.
a set of wires, covered in plastic or rubber, that carries electricity, telephone signals, etc.

data.chText: 我们可以接收多达500个有线电视频道。
data.enText: We can receive up to 500 cable channels.
a message sent by electrical signals and printed out
to send sb a cable n.(4)

ex.chText: 这封电报必须立即发出。
ex.enText: This telegram must be sent at once.

ex.chText: 他收到父亲的一封加急电报。
ex.enText: He received an urgent telegram from his father.
What do you mean by a government telegram?

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指通过电报系统发出的信息，强调具体的一份份电报。

ex.chText: 这封海底电报何时会到巴黎？
ex.enText: When will this cable arrive in Paris?

ex.chText: 他收到了一封从波士顿来的越洋电报。
ex.enText: He received a transoceanic cable from Boston.

ex.chText: 更确切地说，这是一封商业电报。
ex.enText: To be more exact, it is a commercial cable/telegram.

ex.chText: 请给我一张发电报的电报纸好吗?
ex.enText: May I have a form for sending a cable/telegram?

synonyms.bx: 通常指通过海底电缆传输的电报；也可指普通的电报，此时常可与telegram换用。

ex.enText: These islands are connected by telegraph.

ex.chText: 这两个地区之间的电报业务已经中断。
ex.enText: The telegraph between the two regions has been cut.

ex.chText: 1844年塞缪尔·莫尔斯发明了电报。
ex.enText: Telegraph was invented by Samuel Morse in 1844.

synonyms.bx: 不可数名词，强调电报的通信方式或电报业务。

ex.chText: 别担心，我会给他发电报的。
ex.enText: Don't worry, I'll send him a wire.

ex.chText: 今天上午我给妻子发了电报。
ex.enText: I sent a wire to my wife this morning.

synonyms.bx: 与 telegram 同义，但多用于非正式场合。

tr: a very strong thick rope made of twisted hemp or steel wire
a television system that transmits over cables
a conductor for transmitting electrical or optical signals or electric power
television that is transmitted over cable directly to the receiver

value.def: A cable is a thick wire, or a group of wires inside a rubber or plastic covering, which is used to carry electricity or electronic signals.

example.ex: ...strings of coloured lights with weatherproof cable.
example.tran: 搭在防风雨的绝缘电线上的串串彩灯

value.def: A cable is a kind of very strong, thick rope, made of wires twisted together.

example.ex: Steel cable will be used to replace worn ropes.
example.tran: 将用钢缆替换磨损的绳索。

value.def: Cable is used to refer to television systems in which the signals are sent along underground wires rather than by radio waves.

example.ex: They ran commercials on cable systems across the country...
example.tran: 他们在全国的有线电视网上投放商业广告。

example.ex: The channel is only available on cable.
example.tran: 这个频道只有有线电视才能收看。

value.def: A cable is the same as a telegram .

example.ex: She sent a cable to her mother.

value.def: If you cable someone, you send them a message in the form of a telegram.

example.ex: 'Don't do it again,' Franklin cabled her when he got her letter...
example.tran: 富兰克林收到她的信后给她拍了封电报,说:“别再那么做了。”

example.ex: She had to decide whether or not to cable the news to Louis.
example.tran: 她得决定要不要将这个消息电告路易斯。

example.ex: ...a new formula which is being cabled back to capitals for approval.
example.tran: 正通过电报发回各国首都等待批准的新方案

gramarinfo.label: Also V n, V n n, V with quote, V

value.def: If a country, a city, or someone's home is cabled, cables and other equipment are put in place so that the people there can receive cable television.

example.ex: In France, 27 major cities are soon to be cabled...
example.tran: 法国有27座大城市不久将安装有线电视。

example.ex: In the UK, 254,000 homes are cabled.
example.tran: 在英国,有254,000户住户安装了有线电视。
